                        <due></due>
                            <votes>5</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14475108" author="melix" created="Thu, 31 Oct 2013 08:12:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem seems to be related to bridge methods that are generated by the static compiler (Java does something similar). Given that &lt;tt&gt;doSomething()&lt;/tt&gt; is private and called from within an inner class (the closure), a bridge method is generated. Making the method public/protected/package private is a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
